6. Speech and Text Analytics
Speech analytics platforms transform customer conversations into actionable data, identifying recurring issues and behavioral trends.

Step-by-Step Guide to Creating a Unified Customer View
Step 1: Audit Your Existing Data Landscape
Start by identifying:

Where customer data resides

Which systems lack integration

Duplicate data sources

Compliance vulnerabilities

Questions to consider:

Are voice and digital channel data stored separately?

Do agents need to switch between systems during a single interaction?

Is customer sentiment being tracked consistently?

A comprehensive audit prevents future integration failures.

Step 2: Establish a Data Governance Framework
In 2026, U.S. businesses must comply with evolving privacy regulations. A governance framework should include:

Data ownership policies

Access control protocols

Data retention rules

Encryption standards

Strong governance ensures trust and regulatory compliance.

Step 3: Implement API-First Integration
Modern CRM ecosystems rely on API-based integrations to ensure:

Real-time data updates

Cross-platform visibility

Scalability

Vendor flexibility

Avoid legacy batch uploads. Real-time synchronization is critical for AI-driven engagement.

